sentence: The Home Depot, Inc.HD will acquire Interline Brands, Inc. in an all-cash deal worth $1.625 billion.
The acquisition will help Home Depot to better serve the needs of its Pro customers.
The deal, subject to regulatory approval, is expected to conclude in the third quarter of fiscal 2015, which ends on Nov 1, and is expected to be accretive to current's year's bottom line.
The company will provide updated guidance along with its second-quarter financial results on Aug 18, 2015.
Jacksonville, FL-based Interline is one of the foremost names in distributing and direct marketing of broad-line maintenance, repair and operations (MRO) products.
It is owned jointly by Goldman Sachs Capital Partners, P2 Capital Partners, LLC and management.
As per sources, Home Depot, the global leader in home improvement retailing, derives nearly 35% of the annual revenues through its Pro services business.
Improving housing markets have enabled homeowners to take up big ticket home improvement projects, which in turn, have boosted the Pro services business performance.
Going ahead, the markets are expected to continue to recover and thus the acquisition of Interline will help Home Depot to make the most of the opportunity.
Interline boasts of strong outside sales force and fulfilment capabilities in the housing MRO market.
Plus, it has an impressive distribution network of over 90 locations across U.S., Canada and Puerto Rico.
Interline is one of biggest buyouts of the company in a decade.
Apart from the acquisition, the company promoted Bill Lennie to the post of Executive Vice President, Outside Sales and Service.
Lennie currently serves as the president of Canada operations.
In his new post, Lennie will oversee Pro, installation and MRO services business.
At present, Home Depot carries a Zacks Rank #3 (Hold).
Better-ranked stocks in the retail sector include Boot Barn Holdings, Inc.
BOOT , Express Inc. EXPR and DSW Inc. DSW .
While Boot Barn Holdings and Express Inc. sport Zacks Rank #1 (Strong Buy), DSW carries a Zacks Rank #2 (Buy).
